@markusweimer Good catch! For some reason I though I've built this change with VS2013 from command line but turns out I didn't, and it doesn't build in VS2013 indeed.

We can't switch to VS2015 at the moment because we ourselves have at least one cluster (CISL cluster) which only has VS2013. Let's recall this PR for the moment, and discuss switching to VS2015 purposefully on the mailing list.

We should probably also configure two separate AppVeyor builds for 2013 and 2015 to catch such issues automatically
